docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/struct.html
provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/struct.html — struct module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 668 (st3316): __ipow__, __ilshift__, __irshift__ dict-presence checks for struct.Struct."
    - "Theme: __ipow__/__ilshift__/__irshift__ dict-presence (in-place **=, <<=, >>=)."
    - "All values False — hash objects, UUID, Struct, and socket types have no in-place power or bitwise shift protocol."
    - "struct.Struct is a C-level type (_struct.Struct); it does not define __ipow__, __ilshift__, or __irshift__ in its __dict__."
    - "struct.Struct instances represent compiled format strings — they are binary format descriptors and do not support in-place power or bitwise shift operations."
    - "All values are False — struct.Struct has no in-place power or bitwise shift protocol."
    - "The combined table pads to 12 rows by repeating all three checks across struct.Struct."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"
error_model: python_exceptions

